             Kuwaitâ€™s parliament today approved a
budget for the fiscal year through March that increases spending
as the government seeks to boost economic growth by developing
infrastructure.  
 The budget, approved by 39 lawmakers and rejected by 21,
has a projected deficit of 6.6 billion dinars. Spending is
forecast at 16.3 billion dinars and revenue at 9.7 billion
dinars.  
          
          


  


        